High bankruptcy costs weaken creditors' ability to solicit fairer workouts. Nonetheless, from 
\f1 \cf2 [](#lem2)
\f0 \cf0 , workouts are no worse than bankruptcy and liquidation may be better. If one exists, both parties (weakly) prefer to settle; otherwise, insolvent firms sometimes go bankrupt (
\f1 \cf2 [](#prop1)
